%% CV-Screener workflow — source-of-truth design diagram.
%% Approved 2026-05-22. Implementation tracker: CLAUDE.md > Build order.
%%
%% Legend (matches classDef colors below):
%%   neutral   — Input / output (data plumbing, not agents)
%%   llm       — LLM-backed agent
%%   parallel  — LLM agent run as part of the parallel fan-out
%%   det       — Deterministic Python (no LLM call)
%%   hitl      — Human-in-the-loop confidence gate / override
%%   risk      — Risk / safety node (integrity check or HITL sink)

flowchart TD
    A([Input Handler\nCV + JD Upload])
    A --> B

    B[1 · Parsing Agent\nCV + JD → structured JSON]
    B --> CC1

    CC1{Confidence check}
    CC1 -->|low conf| HR1[⚑ Human Review]
    CC1 -->|pass| PAR

    PAR[ ]:::invisible

    PAR --> SM
    PAR --> SN
    PAR --> EX

    SM[2 · Skill Match\nMatched + missing skills]
    SN[3 · Seniority\nJunior / mid / senior]
    EX[4 · Experience\nStrengths + concerns]

    SM --> JOIN
    SN --> JOIN
    EX --> JOIN

    JOIN[ ]:::invisible
    JOIN --> SD

    SD[5 · Integrity & Fairness\nGaps · inconsistencies · bias flags]
    SD --> CC2

    CC2{Confidence check}
    CC2 -->|high risk| HR2[⚑ Human Review]
    CC2 -->|pass| SC

    SC[6 · Scoring Agent\nskills 40% · seniority 30% · domain 20% · edu 10%]
    SC --> HO

    HO[⚑ Human Override\nRecruiter adjusts weights or score]
    HO --> RC

    RC[7 · Recommendation\nShortlist · Hold · Reject]
    RC --> IQ

    IQ[8 · Interview Questions\nTailored to gaps — skip if Reject]
    IQ --> RR

    RR([Recruiter Report UI\nScore breakdown · flags · questions])

    classDef invisible fill:none,stroke:none
    classDef llm fill:#EEEDFE,stroke:#7F77DD,color:#3C3489
    classDef parallel fill:#E1F5EE,stroke:#1D9E75,color:#085041
    classDef det fill:#E6F1FB,stroke:#378ADD,color:#0C447C
    classDef hitl fill:#FAEEDA,stroke:#BA7517,color:#633806
    classDef risk fill:#FAECE7,stroke:#D85A30,color:#712B13
    classDef neutral fill:#F1EFE8,stroke:#888780,color:#444441

    class A,RR neutral
    class B,IQ llm
    class SM,SN,EX parallel
    class SC,RC det
    class CC1,CC2,HO hitl
    class SD,HR1,HR2 risk
